  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AccountScreen
    This is the homescreen which is first presented upon opening the app, and upon logging out.
    ChatScreen
    This is the chatscreen, it is used to chat with a user or a group.
    ChatScreenInput
    Represents the input for the chat screen.
    ContactDisplay
    Displays a contact.
    ContactRequestDisplay
    Displays a contact request.
    CustomButton
    Displays a custom button, used in the navigation bar for the Contacts, Groups, and Logout buttons.
    GuiBase
    This is the starting point for the application It creates the javafx stage, and changes the screen
    HomeScreen
    This is the homescreen.
    HomeScreenInput
    Represents the input for the home screen.
    MessageDisplay

    MUCContactDisplay

    MucInviteScreen

    MUCScreen
    This is the muc screen.
    MUCScreenInput

    NavigationScreen
